title.narrative: BIRTH REGISTRATION

description.narrative: By 2022, the country will have the capacity to reduce under-recording of births in under-fives, supporting the nationwide implementation of the initiative for timely registration in hospitals., which contributes to Access To Justice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, the most vulnerable children and adolescents will be able to exercise their rights to an identity, to live in a family and to be protected against violence.

description.narrative: As a result of persistent advocacy efforts, the Dominican Government, at its highest political level, signed an inter-institutional cooperation agreement to ensure universal birth registration in the presence of the President of the Republic. Despite all the technical, financial, and advocacy assistance efforts, the country did not recover the birth registration rates prior to the COVID-19 pandemic. The birth registration initiative continued to be negatively impacted due to the secondary effects of the pandemic, the rotation of Government authorities, such as the recent cancellation of the coordinating body at the Presidency of the Republic. CONANI will be the new lead. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:14/01/2022
